    / *Key Findings:*:

        - 41.5% (22/53) met Fukuda CFS criteria at 5 years; 13.2% had idiopathic chronic fatigue
        - Important differential diagnoses identified: sleep apnoea (n=5), depression (n=6), anxiety (n=5)
